<h2>Chapter 2: Retainer-Based Pricing. Why 78% of Agencies Use It &#123;#ch2&#125;</h2>
<p>Retainers are the backbone of agency revenue. A 2026 survey by Influencer Marketing Hub found that 78% of digital agencies use retainer-based pricing as their primary model. Up from 64% in 2023.</p>
<p>The reason is straightforward: predictable cash flow.</p>
<h3>How Retainers Work</h3>
<p>The client pays a fixed monthly fee in exchange for ongoing access to the agency's services. That fee is calculated based on estimated hours multiplied by a blended hourly rate, plus a margin for account management and overhead.</p>
